9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 603, L.D. 1488, “An Act Regarding
10 Cannabis Testing and the Manufacture of Cannabis and Hemp Products”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act Regarding Cannabis Testing'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 28-B MRSA §605, sub-§4, as amended by PL 2023, c. 679, Pt. B, §120, is
16 further amended to read:
17 4. No subsequent processing, manufacturing or alteration. Since the performance
18 of the prior testing under subsection 1, the cannabis or cannabis product has not undergone
19 any further processing, manufacturing or alteration that would result in an increase in the
20 concentration of any contaminants or factors identified in section 602, subsection 1 or in
21 any rules adopted by the office pursuant to that section. For purposes of this subsection,
22 "further processing, manufacturing or alteration" does not include the use of cannabis
23 concentrate in the creation of an edible cannabis product, except for testing under section
24 602, subsection 1, paragraph F, and does not include the use of cannabis concentrate in the
25 creation of a cannabis vape cartridge or the use of cannabis flower and cannabis trim in the
26 creation of a prerolled cannabis cigarette.
27 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
28 allocations are made.
29 ADMINISTRATIVE AND FINANCIAL SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
30 Adult Use Cannabis Regulatory Coordination Fund Z264
31 Initiative: Provides funding for quality control testing of cannabis products.
32 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
33 All Other $350,629 $385,692
